CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper December 3, 1960, pg. A3, reads: "Young Adult Business-Professional Women - The young charmers who make up the newly organized club of business and professional women in Pittsburgh were duly installed by officers of the senior club during a brilliant tea at Warren Methodist church recently, when Mrs. Willa Mae Rice, standing ninth from left, second vice president of the senior club, was the featured speaker. Members are, left to right, seated: Elizabeth Brown, Darlene Daniels, Cora Jarvis, Patricia Parker, Sandra Carter, president; Norma Pettigrew, Barbara McCullom, Phyllis Moorman and Eunice McWilson. Standing: Barbara Ficklin, Patricia Prattis, Waunetta Hunt, Kathryn Harris, Carole Griffin, Betty Butler, Betty Wilkins, Rosalyn Pherson, Mrs. Rice, Viola Thompson, Constance Irvin, Gloria Williams, Donna Perkins, Marcia Hill, Jo Ann Turner, Arlean Gantt and Barbara Morant. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Young members of Business - Professional Women, seated from left: Elizabeth Brown, Darlene Daniels, Cora Jarvis, Patricia Parker, Sandra Carter, Norma Pettigrew, Barbara McCullom, Phyllis Moorman, Eunice McWilson; standing: Barbara Ficklin, Patricia Prattis, Waunetta Hunt, Kathryn Harris, Carole Griffin, Betty Butler, Betty Wilkins, Rosalyn Pherson, Willa Mae Rice, Viola Thompson, Constance Irvin, Gloria Williams, Donna Perkins, Marcia Hill, Jo Ann Turner, Arlean Gantt and Barbara Morant posed in Warren Methodist Church
